# Prisma Rules

## Files
- Schema: `apps/api/prisma/schema.prisma`
- Client: `apps/api/src/db/prisma.js` — always import `prisma` from here
- Migrations: `apps/api/prisma/migrations/`

## Schema conventions
```prisma
model MenuItem {
  id        String   @id @default(dbgenerated("gen_random_uuid()")) @db.Uuid
  nameEn    String   @map("name_en")
  nameAr    String   @map("name_ar")
  isActive  Boolean  @default(true) @map("is_active")
  createdAt DateTime @default(now()) @map("created_at") @db.Timestamptz(6)
  updatedAt DateTime @updatedAt @map("updated_at") @db.Timestamptz(6)
  @@map("menu_items")
}
```

## Workflow
1. Edit `schema.prisma`
2. `npm run migrate:dev` (creates migration SQL)
3. `npm run db:generate` (if client stale)
4. Commit schema + migration folder together

## Never
- Edit applied migration SQL files
- Use `pg` Pool directly
- Return `passwordHash` / `pinHash` / `secretHash` in API responses

## Seed
`apps/api/src/db/seed.js` — dev data only; use `prisma.*.upsert`
